tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE Hyperparameters (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    learning_rate FLOAT,
    batch_size INT,
    optimizer VARCHAR(50),
    loss_function VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE model_performance (
    model_id INT,
    validation_accuracy FLOAT,
    training_loss FLOAT,
    validation_loss FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES hyperparameters(model_id)
);

CREATE TABLE ModelMetrics (
    model_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    accuracy FLOAT,
    loss FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE ModelConfigurations (
    config_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id UUID,
    optimizer TEXT,
    activation_func TEXT,
    hidden_layers INT
);

CREATE TABLE hyperparameters (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  model_name STRING,
  learning_rate FLOAT,
  num_layers INT,
  optimizer STRING
);

CREATE TABLE training_data (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  dataset_name STRING,
  num_samples INT,
  input_shape STRING,
  output_shape STRING
);

CREATE TABLE evaluation_metrics (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  model_id UUID,
  accuracy FLOAT,
  precision FLOAT,
  recall FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE model_history (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  model_id UUID,
  training_loss FLOAT,
  validation_loss FLOAT,
  training_time FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE hyperparameters (
    model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    learning_rate FLOAT,
    optimizer VARCHAR,
    batch_size INT,
    num_epochs INT
);

CREATE TABLE model_architecture (
    model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    layers VARCHAR,
    activation_function VARCHAR,
    dropout_rate FLOAT,
    output_size INT
);

CREATE TABLE training_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    loss FLOAT,
    accuracy FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE model_performance (
    performance_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    validation_loss FLOAT,
    validation_accuracy FLOAT,
    test_loss FLOAT,
    test_accuracy FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE experiment_metadata (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    dataset_id INT,
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP
);
